A former Flying Eagles and U-23 captain, Isaac Promise, is dead. The 31-year old who last played for Austin Bold FC in the United Soccer League, USL Championship, died on Wednesday according to a statement released by his American club. Among many other accomplishments, Promise won gold at 2005 Africa Youth Championships in the Republic of Benin as well as a silver same year at the FIFA U20 World Cup. He also led the Nigeria team to the Beijing 2008 Olympics where the country won silver. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Though Promise flourished more with the youth teams, he did have a chance with the Super Eagles where he appeared first in 2009. He earned three caps and scored one goal. Promise played professionally for 14 seasons, much of which was spent in Turkey. He scored a total of 77 club goals during his career.